Artist Forgives Burglar
POSTED: 7:29 pm CDT May 28, 2007

SAN ANTONIO -- An artist said someone burglarized his gallery over the weekend, but he said he's not holding a grudge.

Rick Whittlesey said two paintings that he describes as special pieces in his collection were stolen from his gallery at the intersection of McCullough and Huisache roads.

Whittlesey kept his gallery open on Monday and placed a plywood sign over a window that had been smashed by the burglar with a message that read, "Thief, you are forgiven." The message also incuded the Bible verse Matthew 6:19-21.

Whittlesey said he had planned to sell the paintings, worth more than $2,500, at a July fundraiser.

http://www.ksat.com



